chunks.texto_chunk: --- P√ÅGINA 1 --- [[R-????-?? ]] 241 Northfield Rd. , Kings Norton, Birmingham B30 1EB, England. 5 February 1986. Sr. Presidente Belisario Betancur, Presidente de la Republica, Palacio de Narino, Carrera 8 No.

7-26 Bogota D.E., Colombia. Your Excellency, We are writing to express our extreme concern over the 'disappearance' of **Pablo Caicedo Siachoque** and **Marco Fidel Castro**, reportedly being held in detention at the Base Militar de Tolemaida, Melgar, Tolima department. We respectfully request that the whereabouts of these two men be ascertained, and that they may, in accordance with Articles 9 and 10 of the United Nations Universal Declaration of Human Rights, either be released, or, if they are to be charged with a criminal offence, be brought to court as soon as possible. As lecturers in literature, we have a particular concern for Pablo Caicedo's well-being, but would be most grateful for assurance that both men will receive humane and just treatment. Yours faithfully, **Ruth Hazel** [[firma]] B.R. & R.M. Hazel
